{{for|the painting by [[Titian]] or [[Giorgione]]|Pastoral Concert}} {{Infobox Artwork | image_file=Corot concert champêtre Condé Chantilly.jpg | image_size=300px | title= Woodland music makers | other_language_1 = French | other_title_1 = Le concert champêtre | artist=Jean-Baptiste-Camille Corot | year= 1857 | medium=oil on canvas | height_metric=98 | width_metric=130 | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | city=[[Chantilly, Oise|Chantilly]] | museum=[[Musée Condé]] | owner=[[Institut de France]] }}
'''''Le Concert Champêtre''''' ("Woodland Music-makers") is an [[1857 in art|1857]] painting by French artist [[Jean-Baptiste-Camille Corot]], currently housed in the [[Musée Condé]] of [[Chantilly, Oise|Chantilly]], [[France]]. A reworking of a composition exhibited by Corot in the [[Paris Salon|Salon]] of 1844, the painting was shown in the Salon of 1857.
The painting depicts three women, one with a [[cello]], in the foreground of a forest landscape.
